After the completion of [[Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire]], players can fight a stronger variant of [[the Leviathan]]. An even stronger awakened variant can be fought by climbing the handholds with an [[awakener's orb]] in the player's inventory and selecting "Yes" when prompted.

If the player dies while fighting the Leviathan, their [[grave]] will appear in [[the Scar]] by the rowboat. Players will have their reclamation fee reduced by 75% until they have five kills, after which the standard death cost will apply.

== Requirements ==

* Completion of {{SCP|Quest}} [[Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire]]

== Suggested skills ==

* {{SCP|Ranged|75+}}
* {{SCP|Defence|70+}}
* {{SCP|Hitpoints|80+}}

==Transportation==
The quickest methods of reaching [[the Scar]], where the Leviathan resides, are:
* Using the [[ring of shadows]] to teleport to the Scar, by the abyssal rift. This requires having used the [[scarred tablet]] on it, which is a 1/25 drop from the Leviathan.
* Teleporting to the [[Temple of the Eye (location)|Temple of the Eye]] via the [[amulet of the eye]] (or the [[Minigame Teleport]] for the [[Guardians of the Rift]] minigame), then reaching the Scar via the [[Catalytic Guardian]].
* Reaching the Temple of the Eye via the portal in the [[Wizards' Tower]] basement ([[necklace of passage]] teleport or [[fairy ring]] code {{Fairycode|dis}}).

==Fight overview==
